    "intro": "Interpretation moves from what the text says to what it means — from observation of words and structures to discernment of authorial intent in its canonical context. Ruth 2 is simultaneously a historical narrative, a wisdom text about covenant loyalty, and a theological statement about how God's providence operates through human agents. The movements below follow the chapter's three natural divisions: the providential arrangement of the encounter (2:1-7), the encounter itself and what Boaz reveals in it (2:8-17), and Naomi's theological interpretation of what has occurred (2:18-23).",
